wikipedia_page.main: John Arthur Deed (12 September 1901 – 19 October 1980), known as Jack Deed, was an English amateur cricketer who played for Kent County Cricket Club between 1924 and 1930. He was born in Sevenoaks in Kent in 1901.

response: Outside cricket, he was a fine rackets player, winning the Public School's rackets pairs in 1920 with Jack Deed.
